# Portal Retail Design System

This repository IS the design system. It defines all rules, tokens, components, patterns, and guidelines for the `portal-retail-frontend` Angular project.

## How the AI must use this repository

When asked to generate any Angular code for portal-retail, ALWAYS:

1. **Read the relevant design system file first** using the GitHub MCP or filesystem MCP before generating code
2. Apply all rules from the matching file
3. Never deviate from the patterns unless explicitly instructed

### File reference map

| Task | Read this file first |
|---|---|
| Any color usage | `tokens/colors.md` |
| Any text/font | `tokens/typography.md` |
| Any layout/spacing | `tokens/spacing.md` |
| Button component | `components/button.md` |
| Data table / listing | `components/dynamic-table.md` |
| Page title / heading | `components/heading.md` |
| Page layout | `components/content-wrapper.md` |
| KPI cards / stats | `components/stat-card.md` |
| Create a listing page | `patterns/listing-page.md` |
| Create a form page | `patterns/form-page.md` |
| File/folder structure | `guidelines/file-structure.md` |
| Angular architecture | `guidelines/angular-architecture.md` |
| Tooling / CLI | `guidelines/tooling.md` |

## Quick Reference — Non-negotiable Rules

- Standalone components only (NO `standalone: true` in decorator — it's default)
- `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush` on every component
- `inject()` function, never constructor injection
- `input()` and `output()` functions, never `@Input()` / `@Output()`
- Signals for all local state (`signal()`, `computed()`, `update()`)
- Native control flow only (`@if`, `@for`, `@switch`) — never `*ngIf`, `*ngFor`
- `[class]` and `[style]` bindings — never `[ngClass]` or `[ngStyle]`
- PrimeNG → Angular Material → Bootstrap (in this priority for new UI)
- Reactive Forms only — never Template-driven
- All page content wrapped in `<content-wrapper>`
- `app-button` for all buttons — never raw `<button>` without `bt-*` class
- `eretail-dynamic-table` for all data lists — never raw `mat-table` in pages
